    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a good point about the environmental degradation—it's possible some are being tossed in the scrap bin without being logged. \n\nBut I'm still stuck on the randomness. The discrepancies aren't tied to any specific staff changes or environmental shifts. It's almost like there's a tiny, invisible leak in the system. If we rule out theft, data errors, and environmental damage, what else could explain these small, unexplained \"disappearances\" of stock that just don't leave any forensic trail?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
