      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Given all evidence points to irregular but small losses, we should examine the accuracy and reliability of the technologies used for tracking inventory. Scanning issues in the WMS could misrepresent actual counts. Inspect the calibration of equipment, such as barcode scanners, making sure they are operating correctly and consistently. Also, consider implementing a double-check process or using a redundant system to validate stock levels. Lastly, although difficult, conduct an unannounced spot-check to catch any real-time movements that might not be documented yet. Under high-value components, it's also prudent to enhance the physical security measures unexpectedly to deter sensitive stock taking.",
